procedures.name: Venipuncture

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of venous blood for laboratory analysis, including pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), clinical laboratory tests, and genetic sampling.

procedures.name: Urine Sample Collection
procedures.label: Urine Test
procedures.description: Collection of urine for urinalysis, pregnancy testing, and drug screening.

procedures.name: Insulin Infusion to Induce Hypoglycemia
procedures.label: Insulin Infusion
procedures.description: Intravenous (IV) infusion of insulin to induce a controlled state of hypoglycemia for study purposes.

procedures.name: Glucagon Administration
procedures.label: Study Drug Administration
procedures.description: Administration of study treatment, either Nasal LY900018 or Intramuscular Glucagon (IMG).

procedures.name: Intravenous Glucose Supplementation
procedures.label: IV Glucose
procedures.description: Administration of intravenous (IV) glucose if a patient experiences signs and symptoms of severe hypoglycemia requiring intervention.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Monitoring
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Measurement of supine blood pressure, pulse rate, and body temperature at specified time points.

procedures.name: Bedside Plasma Glucose Monitoring
procedures.label: Bedside PG Monitoring
procedures.description: Frequent monitoring of plasma glucose levels at the bedside for safety during the hypoglycemia induction procedure and post-treatment.

procedures.name: Electrocardiogram

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Recording of single and triplicate 12-lead ECGs to monitor cardiac electrical activity.

procedures.name: Laboratory Testing
procedures.label: Lab Tests
procedures.description: Includes clinical serology, hematology, clinical chemistry, urinalysis, HbA1c, pregnancy test, FSH, and ethanol testing.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A general physical examination performed at screening.

procedures.name: Nasal Inspection
procedures.label: Nasal Inspection
procedures.description: Visual inspection of the nasal passages before and after study drug administration.

procedures.name: Injection-Site Assessment
procedures.label: Injection-Site Assessment
procedures.description: Assessment of the injection site for patients receiving Intramuscular Glucagon (IMG).

procedures.name: Edinburgh Hypoglycemia Scale
procedures.label: Hypoglycemia Questionnaire
procedures.description: Administration of a questionnaire to evaluate the recovery from clinical symptoms of hypoglycemia.

procedures.name: Height and Weight Measurement
procedures.label: Height and Weight
procedures.description: Measurement of patient's height at screening and weight at specified visits.

medicalDevices.name: Nasal Dosing Device
medicalDevices.label: LY900018 Device
medicalDevices.description: A single-use, nasal dosing device that delivers 3 mg glucagon powder for absorption through the nasal mucosa.

medicalDevices.name: Syringe and Needle
medicalDevices.label: IM Injection Kit
medicalDevices.description: Device used for intramuscular (IM) injection of reconstituted glucagon powder.

medicalDevices.name: Intravenous Infusion System
medicalDevices.label: IV Infusion Setup
medicalDevices.description: System used for the intravenous (IV) infusion of insulin and glucose.

medicalDevices.name: Bedside Glucose Monitor
medicalDevices.label: Glucometer
medicalDevices.description: Device used for frequent bedside monitoring of plasma glucose (PG) levels.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead Electrocardiogram Machine
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Diagnostic device used to perform single and triplicate 12-lead ECGs.

medicalDevices.name: Continuous Subcutaneous Insulin Infusion Pump
medicalDevices.label: CSII Pump
medicalDevices.description: An insulin pump used for continuous subcutaneous insulin infusion as part of a patient's standard therapy.
